Description: Five fragments from Fikellura painted pottery neck-amphora: three separate, one formed of seven joined fragments (a), one formed of six joined fragments (b). (A) shoulder, tongues: row of birds (the two birds on the left of simpler type). (B) belly: two rows of crescents. Three separate fragments: crescents.
Curator's comments: Two fragments with crescents not illustrated in CVA. For the birds with outline body compare the oinochoe New York C.P.55A (BSA xxxiv, 93-95, figs. 19-20). BSA xxxiv, 12 (G 3a), 14. Attributed to Mykonos Group. Mykonos group (G 30). Middle or third quarter of sixth century.
